ryo adoption advances ambitious political goals for expanding the influence of conservative Christian values and power.Conceiving Christian America is the first book on embryo adoption tracing how this powerful social movement draws on white saviorist tropes in their aims to reconceive personhood, with drastic consequences for reproductive rights and justice. Documenting the practices, narratives, and beliefs that move embryos from freezers to uteruses, this book wields anthropological wariness as a tool for confronting the multiple tactics of the Christian Right. Timely and provocative, Conceiving Christian America presents a bold and nuanced examination of a family-making process focused on conceiving a Christian nation.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aAdoptionxMoral and ethical aspects. 0aAdoptionxReligious aspectsxChristianity. 0aFertilization in vitro, Human. 0aFrozen human embryosxMoral and ethical aspects. 0aHuman embryoxTransplantationxMoral and ethical aspects. 0aHuman reproductive technologyxReligious aspectsxChristianity. 7aFAMILY & RELATIONSHIPS / Adoption & Fostering.2bisacsh  aBulletin Board System (BBS).  aChristian Right.  aDigital humanities.  aPolitical activism.  aTransgender history.  aUS politics.  aWeb history.  aantiabortion activists.  aantiabortion movement.  aassisted reproductive technologies.  acloud storage.  acontent delivery networks.  adiscourse.  adownload speeds.  aembryo adoption.  aethnographic methods.  afeminist anthropology.  aglobal media.  ain vitro fertilization.  ainfrastructure.  alegal scholars.  anet neutrality.  apersonhood politics.  apro-life movement.  areproductive politics.  asaviorism.  ascience and technology studies (STS).  awhite pro-life evangelicalism.  awhite saviorism.08iTitle is p